<task id="task-6600" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Bypass certificate validation in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><note class="- topic/note "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">Available for Chrome and Firefox.</li></ul></note><ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> supports the capability to bypass certificate validation so that users with protected network policy can work with <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> as usual. The configuration here applies for Web Service tests. <p class="- topic/p ">To configure certificate settings, do as follows:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-project" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-settings" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> &gt; <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-network" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image href="ks-841-certificate-settings.png" width="700" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">network settings</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Certificate Settings</uicontrol> section, choose <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Bypass certificate validation</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply and Close</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps></taskbody></task>